<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-01-23T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-01-23T16:00:00-05:00" n="472" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d472">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">882.73/14: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-01-23T16:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">January
                                            23, 1919, 4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>Please ascertain promptly who has the custody of the Pernambuco end
                                of the former German cable connecting Pernambuco with Monrovia,
                                Liberia. Cable reply.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>